{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":5291,"name":"","username":"rogerdv","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/r/eb8c5e/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-03-11T16:46:23.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIm trying to figure out how to make my items fit the attach bone more exactly, to avoid finding the correct offset and rotation, and I have a doubt about the difference between both settings in the exporter. Local means that the exported geometry has its own coordinates, starting at 0,0,0 or something like that?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:05.761Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":5,"readers_count":4,"score":6.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":919,"topic_slug":"difference-between-global-and-local-in-exporter","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":76,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":5292,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-03-11T18:06:24.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou are using the reattiva‚Äôs exporter or AssetImporter tool ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLocal means that the exported geometry has its own coordinates\u003cbr\u003e\nI guess local means that vertex positions will be represents as offset‚Äôs from origin (pivot - in 3dmax terms) of object.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eglobal mean that in geometry data the vertexes position will be writing as offset from global vector3(0,0,0)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut I found that some times( actually most times:) ) we need local geometry but not local Node‚Äôs position settings.\u003cbr\u003e\nfor this issue i‚Äôm made cup of fixes for fork of reattiva‚Äôs exporter\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003elink: \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/MonkeyFirst/Urho3D-Blender\"\u003egithub.com/MonkeyFirst/Urho3D-Blender\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut before start export need setup some specific settings:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[spoiler]Select object(s) that need to export\u003cbr\u003e\nthen choice Object -\u0026gt;Apply -\u0026gt; Rotation \u0026amp; Scale ( not Location! this override vertex data in geometry as offset from global(0,0,0) )\u003cbr\u003e\nthen open settings set Front View = ‚ÄúBack‚Äù (only this work propertly, because i‚Äôm still not found the view‚Äôs right matrix to mulply, currently just do swap of axis )\u003cbr\u003e\norigin = local\u003cbr\u003e\nobject = only selected\u003cbr\u003e\nExport Urho prefabs = True\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://savepic.su/5360750.htm\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://savepic.su/5360750m.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"\" height=\"\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003esetup other setting as you needed\u003cbr\u003e\npress export\u003cbr\u003e\nyou got an Data/Scenes/%Scene%.xml named as Scene.name in Blender\u003cbr\u003e\nin this Scene you need find Node named as ‚ÄúScene‚Äù you must save it as local node to Data/Objects/ as prefab.\u003cbr\u003e\nWell, that‚Äôs all.\u003cbr\u003e\nUse this prefab in you main scene, the nodes in it are must already placed as they placed in blender scene.[/spoiler]\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:05.815Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":5,"readers_count":4,"score":1.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":919,"topic_slug":"difference